<span id="freeTextContainer12613355439612858569">&quot;𝘐 𝘸𝘢𝘴 𝘴𝘶𝘳𝘦 𝘵𝘩𝘢𝘵 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘎𝘰𝘥 𝘸𝘦 𝘩𝘢𝘥 𝘬𝘯𝘰𝘸𝘯 𝘪𝘯 𝘗𝘢𝘭𝘦𝘴𝘵𝘪𝘯𝘦 𝘩𝘢𝘥 𝘭𝘦𝘧𝘵 𝘪𝘵 𝘵𝘰𝘰, 𝘢𝘯𝘥 𝘸𝘢𝘴 𝘢 𝘳𝘦𝘧𝘶𝘨𝘦𝘦 𝘪𝘯 𝘴𝘰𝘮𝘦 𝘱𝘭𝘢𝘤𝘦 𝘵𝘩𝘢𝘵 𝘐 𝘥𝘪𝘥 𝘯𝘰𝘵 𝘬𝘯𝘰𝘸...&quot;<br/><br/>I read this collection last year, not able to fully grasp the size of the Palestinian tragedy. This year, with Palestine returning to the global spotlight in May, I read more about the country and felt I needed to read this collection again, now with much better understanding. <br/><br/>I thorougly enjoyed all seven of its stories, Kanafani&apos;s writing surpassed all my expectations, and</span>
  <span id="freeText12613355439612858569" style="display:none">"𝘐 𝘸𝘢𝘴 𝘴𝘶𝘳𝘦 𝘵𝘩𝘢𝘵 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘎𝘰𝘥 𝘸𝘦 𝘩𝘢𝘥 𝘬𝘯𝘰𝘸𝘯 𝘪𝘯 𝘗𝘢𝘭𝘦𝘴𝘵𝘪𝘯𝘦 𝘩𝘢𝘥 𝘭𝘦𝘧𝘵 𝘪𝘵 𝘵𝘰𝘰, 𝘢𝘯𝘥 𝘸𝘢𝘴 𝘢 𝘳𝘦𝘧𝘶𝘨𝘦𝘦 𝘪𝘯 𝘴𝘰𝘮𝘦 𝘱𝘭𝘢𝘤𝘦 𝘵𝘩𝘢𝘵 𝘐 𝘥𝘪𝘥 𝘯𝘰𝘵 𝘬𝘯𝘰𝘸..."<br /><br />I read this collection last year, not able to fully grasp the size of the Palestinian tragedy. This year, with Palestine returning to the global spotlight in May, I read more about the country and felt I needed to read this collection again, now with much better understanding. <br /><br />I thorougly enjoyed all seven of its stories, Kanafani's writing surpassed all my expectations, and I was impressed by how powerfully his writing is rooted in Palestinian history, culture and folklore. He truly was one of the greatest Palestinian authors.</span>
